This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it deals with syntactic rules in human language and the acquisition of language. It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) because it uses recurrent neural networks to simulate language acquisition. Additionally, it could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) because of the use of neural networks. Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CC) because it deals with the intersection of computation and language.
